The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to sequences of numbers, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. The problem of finding superlinear lower bounds is a fundamental question in computational complexity, which could place the paper in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) category. The use of empirical evidence to support the lower bounds could also suggest the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) category. Finally, the paper deals with reductions between two problems, which could place it in the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.IT (Information Theory) categories.
